# Lab 07 -- Part 0: your personal test gateway + runner.
#
# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) and fill it in:
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Then bring the test pair up with:  ./scripts/setup.sh
# (or, if the dev stack is already running:  docker compose --profile test up -d)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The ONE value you must set. Lowercase, no spaces -- it becomes part of a
# GitHub runner label and a container name.
#
# Everything derives from it:
#   your runner's label     ->  <yourname>-local
#   your runner's name      ->  lab07-test-<yourname>
#   your workflow's runs-on ->  [self-hosted, <yourname>-local]   (Part 0 step 3)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
LAB_USER=yourname

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Registering a runner on the shared repo needs repo-admin rights, which
# contributors do not have -- so ONE of these two comes from Sam or Jasper.
#
#   RUNNER_GITHUB_PAT  a fine-grained PAT scoped to only this repo.
#                      Preferred: the runner re-registers itself on every
#                      restart, unattended.
#   RUNNER_TOKEN       a short-lived registration token (valid 1 hour).
#                      Fine for today: the registration persists in a volume,
#                      so it only has to work once. The runner image prefers
#                      the PAT when both are set.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RUNNER_GITHUB_PAT=
RUNNER_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Overrides -- only uncomment if you have a reason.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your runner's second label. Your test-<yourname>.yml's runs-on must match
# this EXACTLY, or your job waits forever for a runner that does not exist.
#RUNNER_LABEL=yourname-local

# What the runner is called under Settings -> Actions -> Runners.
#RUNNER_NAME=lab07-test-yourname

# Which repo the runner registers against.
#REPO_URL=https://github.com/Mustry-Academy/cicd-lab-07-multi-gateway-deploy
